## Discoveries

- The codebase already has strong signal wiring:
  - Shared logic in `src/run_signal_wiring.rs` (`RunSignalWiring`, `SignalProcess`, `SignalRevoker`).
  - `main` run loop (`run_child_with_os_signals`) uses this wiring.
  - `integration_runtime::forward_sigterm_then_escalate_with_os_signals` also uses this wiring.
- Existing integration signal report was too narrow:
  - `SignalHandlingReport` only had `forwarded_sigterm` and `double_signal_escalated`.
  - This was insufficient for parity assertions across `SIGTERM`, `SIGINT`, and `SIGHUP`.
- During TDD:
  - Newly added parity tests initially failed at compile time because `SignalHandlingReport` lacked `forwarded_sigint`/`forwarded_sighup`.
  - After adding fields, one test still failed due to signal contamination/noise from process-level pending signals.
  - Fixed by filtering integration loop signal handling using per-signal expected counts (`remaining_parent_signals` map) so only injected test sequence signals are consumed.
- Full `cargo test` run showed one failure:
  - `formatting_gate_tests::cargo_fmt_check_passes_cleanly` failed due to formatting drift in `src/main.rs` around newly added tests.
  - This is currently the blocker before claiming all-green.
- Repo working tree contains many unrelated modified/untracked files; care needed to commit only bead-related changes.

